Description: Neck fragment of pottery transport amphora with part of handle scar. Clay near fine, micaceous, light brown. Roughly rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 27a, 16. Appears to be the same stamp as on an intact jar found on Kos, in an area of amphora production.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1250)
